{{about|the electronic device|bootlegs of audio|Bootleg recording}}
[[File:فوناك.jpg|thumb|A hearing aid with an audio boot.]]
An '''audio boot''' or '''audio shoe''' is an electronic device used by the [[hard of hearing]] with [[hearing aid]]s; hearing aids often come with a special set of metal contacts for audio input. Typically the audio boot will fit around the end of the hearing aid (a behind-the-ear model, as in-the-ear do not afford any purchase for the connection) link these with another device, like an FM system or a [[cellphone]] or even a [[digital audio player]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nchearingloss.org/boot.htm?fromncshhh|title=Boot Definition|website=www.nchearingloss.org|access-date=2017-06-02}}</ref>

