{{for|the award given by the Italian Physical Society (Società Italiana di Fisica)|Enrico Fermi Prize}}
The '''Enrico Fermi Award''' is an award honoring scientists of international stature for their lifetime achievement in the development, use, or production of [[energy]]. It is administered by the U.S. government's [[United States Department of Energy|Department of Energy]]. The recipient receives $50,000, a certificate signed by the President and the Secretary of Energy, and a gold medal featuring the likeness of [[Enrico Fermi]].
