[[File:IC Extractor.JPG|thumb|IC extractor tool, which is used for removing [[Plastic leaded chip carrier|PLCC]] ICs]]

An '''IC extractor''' is a tool for safely and quickly removing [[integrated circuits]] (ICs) from their [[IC socket (disambiguation)|socket]]s. The main purpose of using this tool is to avoid bending the socket pins<ref name="IC_Extractor"/> and to avoid damage through [[electrostatic discharge]] (ESD).
[[File:PLCC Removal.gif|thumb|thumb|A PLCC package being removed from its socket with a PLCC extractor]]

